    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "Job Title: Senior Customer Finance Analyst\n\nCompany Overview:\n\nPrompt is revolutionizing healthcare by delivering highly automated and modern software to rehab therapy businesses, the teams within, and the patients they serve. As the fastest-growing company in the space and the new standard in healthcare technology,We strive to attract top talent who share our vision and values. As we continue to grow, we are seeking a proactive and results-driven Talent Acquisition Specialist to join our dynamic team.\n\nJob Description:\n\nAs a Senior Customer Finance Analyst at Prompt, you will be a key driver of scalability within our finance department. Reporting to the Customer Finance Lead, you will go beyond day-to-day transaction management to lead process optimization and automation initiatives. You will act as a subject matter expert, using your high attention to detail and analytical mindset to solve complex billing logic issues and ensure our financial operations are built for rapid growth.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\n1. Revenue Operations \u0026 Advanced Invoicing\n\n - Oversee the end-to-end invoicing lifecycle, ensuring 100% accuracy in complex billing cycles and compliance with bespoke customer agreements.\n\n - Identify bottlenecks in the billing workflow and partner with the Finance Lead to design and implement automated solutions within NetSuite/QuickBooks.\n\n - Perform root-cause analysis on recurring billing discrepancies and implement permanent process fixes while communicating with leadership on the context of the issues.\n\n2. Scalable Customer Onboarding\n\n - Audit and validate customer agreements to ensure financial data integrity before account creation.\n\n - Create customer accounts and process sensitive financial data accurately.\n\n - Identify bottlenecks in the customer creation workflow and partner with the Finance Lead to design and implement automated solutions within NetSuite/QuickBooks and other softwares such as HubSpot, SpotDraft, etc.\n\n3. Strategic Customer Support \u0026 Problem Solving\n\n - Manage high-priority or complex customer financial inquiries, translating technical issues into clear, professional communication.\n\n - Collaborate cross-functionally with multiple departments to resolve structural billing hurdles for clients.\n\n4. Systems \u0026 Data Management\n\n - Maintain the integrity of the customer master data, ensuring clean reporting for Senior Management.\n\n - Support the Customer Finance Lead in ad-hoc projects, including ERP migrations, system integrations (AP/AR tools), and the creation of standardized training documentation for future team growth.\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\n - Education: Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics, or a related field.\n\n - Experience: 3+ years of experience in Accounts Receivable, Billing, or Revenue Operations (senior-level ownership expected).\n\n - Technical Mastery: Advanced proficiency in NetSuite and QuickBooks \u0026 Expert Excel/Google Sheets skills- must be comfortable with complex formulas, pivot tables, and data modeling to identify trends or errors.\n\n - Problem-Solving: A proven track record of taking a manual process and developing as well as executing a better process through automation or workflow redesign.\n\n - Meticulous Attention to Detail: An obsession with accuracy; you are the person who catches the $0.01 discrepancy before it becomes a client issue.\n\n - Communication: Ability to distill complex financial data into actionable insights for stakeholders and senior leadership.\n\nPerks – What You Can Expect\n\n - Competitive salaries\n\n - Remote/hybrid flexibility\n\n - Potential equity for outstanding performance\n\n - Flexible PTO\n\n - Company-wide sponsored lunches\n\n - Company-paid disability and life insurance\n\n - Family and medical leave\n\n - Medical, dental, and vision insurance\n\n - Discounted pet insurance\n\n - FSA/DCA and commuter benefits\n\n - 401(k)\n\n - Complimentary subscription to digital fitness classes and wellness content\n\n - Recovery suite at HQ with cold plunge, sauna, and shower\n\nHere at Prompt, we are committed to fostering a fair and respectful work environment. As part of this commitment, it is our policy not to hire individuals from Prompt Customers unless they have obtained their current employer's explicit consent. We believe in upholding strong professional relationships and respecting the agreements and commitments our customers have with their employees. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation regarding this policy.Please don't hesitate to inquire with our team.\n\nPrompt Therapy Solutions, Inc is an equal opportunity employer, indiscriminate of race, color, religion, ethnicity, ancestry, national origin, sex, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, disability, medical condition, or any other protected characteristic. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees\n\nPrompt Therapy Solutions, Inc is an E-Verify Employer.\n\n\n",
